# Netlify response headers
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Purpose: ensure staff see the latest version of the app after a deploy,
# without needing to hard-refresh their browser.
#
# How it works: "no-cache" does NOT mean "don't cache." It means the
# browser keeps a local copy but must ask the server "is this still
# current?" before using it. The server replies with a tiny 304 (Not
# Modified) if nothing changed → instant load. If the file changed → a
# fresh copy is fetched. End result: updates appear immediately, without
# any extra bandwidth cost on unchanged visits.
#
# We apply this only to index.html (and the root path that serves it),
# because that's the single file that contains the whole app. External
# assets (Firebase, Google Fonts) manage their own caching on CDNs.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

/index.html
  Cache-Control: no-cache, must-revalidate

/
  Cache-Control: no-cache, must-revalidate
